- I'm here for lack of a better idea.

246
00:25:33,282 --> 00:25:35,074
- That's a shame.
- Not really.

247
00:25:35,242 --> 00:25:37,493
Peace Corps types only
stay around long enough...

248
00:25:37,661 --> 00:25:39,579
...to realize they're not helping anyone.

249
00:25:39,747 --> 00:25:41,623
Government only wants
to stay in power...

250
00:25:41,790 --> 00:25:44,667
...until they've stolen enough
to go into exile somewhere else.

251
00:25:44,835 --> 00:25:47,462
And the rebels, they're not sure
they want to take over.

252
00:25:47,630 --> 00:25:49,964
Otherwise,
they'd have to govern this mess.

253
00:25:50,132 --> 00:25:52,467
- But TIA, right, M'Ed?
- TIA.

254
00:25:52,635 --> 00:25:53,843
What's TIA?

255
00:25:54,470 --> 00:25:58,389
- "This is Africa," huh?
- Right.

256
00:25:58,974 --> 00:26:01,434
- You want another?
- Sure.

257
00:26:05,231 --> 00:26:07,774
So which one are you?

258
00:26:09,235 --> 00:26:12,487
- Smuggler?
- Am I?

259
00:26:12,655 --> 00:26:15,615
Somehow you don't strike me
as the UNICEF type.

260
00:26:16,659 --> 00:26:18,618
How about soldier of fortune?

261
00:26:19,078 --> 00:26:21,663
Or is that too much of a cliche?

262
00:26:21,830 --> 00:26:23,164
Diamonds?

263
00:26:23,832 --> 00:26:27,460
- If I told you I was a missionary...?
- For Van De Kaap?

264
00:26:29,171 --> 00:26:31,756
Better watch that type of talk,
Miss Bowen.

265
00:26:31,924 --> 00:26:35,009
In America, it's bling-bling,
but out here, it's bling-bang, huh?

266
00:26:35,302 --> 00:26:38,429
I wouldn't want you
getting in any trouble.

267
00:26:39,682 --> 00:26:41,975
How much trouble
do you think I would get into...

268
00:26:42,142 --> 00:26:45,395
...for talking about blood diamonds?

269
00:26:48,190 --> 00:26:51,276
- You're a journalist.
- That's right.

270
00:26:55,197 --> 00:26:56,823
Piss off, huh?

271
00:27:01,161 --> 00:27:04,414
For five years, this country has reported
almost no diamond exports...

272
00:27:04,581 --> 00:27:08,251
...while Liberia, right next door,
has exported 2 billion dollars' worth.

273
00:27:08,419 --> 00:27:11,462
Very odd, considering that Liberia
has no diamonds to speak of.

274
00:27:11,630 --> 00:27:12,630
I'm shocked.

275
00:27:12,798 --> 00:27:16,134
Van De Kaap denies trading blood
diamonds, but admits it's impossible...

276
00:27:16,302 --> 00:27:20,638
...to tell where a diamond comes from
unless their smuggler gets caught.

277
00:27:20,806 --> 00:27:22,515
What do you want from me, huh?

278
00:27:22,683 --> 00:27:27,228
You know all about Van De Kaap.
Help me out. Off the record.

279
00:27:27,438 --> 00:27:31,899
Well, off the record, I like to get kissed
before I get fucked, huh?

280
00:27:34,486 --> 00:27:35,695
Shit.

281
00:28:09,021 --> 00:28:12,523
- Cordell. How is it, Shona?
- Long time, pal.

282
00:28:12,691 --> 00:28:16,069
- How's Alice?
- She's well, thanks.

283
00:28:16,236 --> 00:28:18,071
Tim must be in school, right?

284
00:28:18,238 --> 00:28:20,573
- Big kids, big problems, you know?
- Yeah, yeah.

285
00:28:20,741 --> 00:28:23,326
I heard you got into a spot of trouble
in the bush, huh?

286
00:28:23,494 --> 00:28:25,912
Well, you know the bush, right, bru?

287
00:28:26,663 --> 00:28:29,248
- Company doing well?
- Can't complain.

288
00:28:29,416 --> 00:28:32,043
Eleven wars in the continent.
We're keeping busy.

289
00:28:32,211 --> 00:28:34,629
So, what, you're here on holiday, huh?

290
00:28:36,340 --> 00:28:38,257
- How's the colonel?
- He sends his regards.

291
00:28:38,425 --> 00:28:42,136
Good, good. Score us a loose, huh?

292
00:28:43,222 --> 00:28:45,431
Smoking will kill you, bru.

293
00:28:45,682 --> 00:28:46,933
Only if I live, right?

294
00:28:52,272 --> 00:28:54,148
That's for breaking my TV, bru.

295
00:28:59,029 --> 00:29:02,573
Tell the colonel he'll get his money.
I'll come see him soon.

296
00:29:09,331 --> 00:29:10,540
Ten more.

297
00:29:10,707 --> 00:29:13,626
Come. Come.

298
00:29:19,716 --> 00:29:21,217
Go on.

299
00:29:35,399 --> 00:29:39,360
Dia. Dia. Come here.
Get away from there.

300
00:29:39,945 --> 00:29:42,613
Go. Go, Mama.

301
00:29:42,781 --> 00:29:44,699
Stay down.

302
00:29:48,454 --> 00:29:49,954
Please...

303
00:29:50,330 --> 00:29:53,207
I must talk to someone. My family's
name is not on the list.

304
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:54,876
Go to Kissy, there is another list.

305
00:29:55,461 --> 00:29:57,253
I have been to Kissy, and Waterloo, and
Port Loko, and-

306
00:29:57,671 --> 00:29:59,714
Talk to the whites.

307
00:30:02,843 --> 00:30:04,510
Excuse me,
my name's Solomon Vandy-

308
00:30:04,678 --> 00:30:06,762
- Check the list.
- I have checked the list.

309
00:30:06,930 --> 00:30:11,392
- File papers at the Office for Refugees.
- Sir, I have filed papers with the office.

310
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:13,561
Then God help you,
because I can't.

311
00:30:13,729 --> 00:30:14,812
- Please, sir-
- Next.

312
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:17,106
- Sir- Sir, no, please.
- Hey, hey. Me, me, me.

313
00:30:17,274 --> 00:30:21,068
Husband here. One year we look.

314
00:30:25,574 --> 00:30:27,742
Hurry, Mom. Go.

315
00:30:32,915 --> 00:30:34,248
Dia! Dia!

316
00:30:34,416 --> 00:30:35,416
- Jassie!
- Dia!

317
00:30:35,584 --> 00:30:37,210
- Mama!
- Dia!

318
00:30:37,377 --> 00:30:39,545
Jassie! Mama!

319
00:30:53,185 --> 00:30:55,937
Cape Town,
South Africa

320
00:31:01,777 --> 00:31:04,612
He's been waiting.
What took you?

321
00:31:05,322 --> 00:31:08,699
What are you gonna do,
shoot me right here, huh, Shona?

322
00:31:08,867 --> 00:31:11,953
Now, don't be a wanker, man. Get in.

323
00:31:44,027 --> 00:31:46,445
- Hello, Danny.
- Colonel.

324
00:31:46,613 --> 00:31:48,406
You look well.

325
00:31:48,574 --> 00:31:51,742
Clean living and a pure heart,
I suppose, huh?

326
00:31:52,077 --> 00:31:53,786
Walk with me.

327
00:31:55,539 --> 00:31:58,374
It seems the rebels have taken back
the diamond fields, Danny.

328
00:31:58,542 --> 00:32:00,876
The government
of Sierra Leone has contracted us...

329
00:32:01,044 --> 00:32:03,004
...to go in there
and take the rebels down.

330
00:32:03,171 --> 00:32:04,797
So you sell the rebels weapons...

331
00:32:04,965 --> 00:32:07,633
...the government hires you
when they use them? Nice, sir.

332
00:32:08,093 --> 00:32:10,970
I assume you're asking
for mining concessions, huh?

333
00:32:11,138 --> 00:32:14,265
We save the government,
they show their gratitude.

334
00:32:14,433 --> 00:32:16,726
And you get rich, right?

335
00:32:21,023 --> 00:32:22,607
How long have I known you, Danny?

336
00:32:23,025 --> 00:32:26,193
I was... I was 19, sir.

337
00:32:26,445 --> 00:32:30,990
And you survived.
A lot of boys didn't. Why is that?

338
00:32:32,367 --> 00:32:35,036
Just lucky, I guess.

339
00:32:36,955 --> 00:32:41,834
No, you were a good soldier.
But I made you better, didn't I?

340
00:32:45,213 --> 00:32:46,631
Yes, sir. Yes, you did.

341
00:32:46,798 --> 00:32:49,842
And over the years,
didn't I protect you...

342
00:32:50,218 --> 00:32:54,221
...teach you about diamonds,
cut you in on the deals?

343
00:32:54,389 --> 00:32:58,059
- Some might call it that, yeah.
- But not you...

344
00:32:59,019 --> 00:33:02,688
...because you done with me now, eh?
On to bigger things.

345
00:33:05,817 --> 00:33:08,277
I need a man that knows
his way around up there.

346
00:33:08,445 --> 00:33:12,239
Unless, of course,
you wanna cut me in. Something pink?

347
00:33:13,283 --> 00:33:14,825
Sir...

348
00:33:14,993 --> 00:33:17,119
Our deal went bad,
and you owe me money.

349
00:33:17,287 --> 00:33:19,038
I'll take a stone as payment.

350
00:33:19,206 --> 00:33:23,084
Look, do you think if I found a stone
like that, I'd still be on this continent?

351
00:33:23,251 --> 00:33:27,088
- Come on.
- Danny, give me your hand.

352
00:33:30,092 --> 00:33:33,803
That's red earth. It's in our skin.

353
00:33:34,262 --> 00:33:36,681
The Shona say the color
comes from all the blood...

354
00:33:36,848 --> 00:33:39,433
...that's being spilled
fighting over the land.

355
00:33:41,436 --> 00:33:46,023
This is home.
You'll never leave Africa.

356
00:33:48,777 --> 00:33:51,445
If you say so, sir.

357
00:34:06,962 --> 00:34:10,631
So, what did you do, bury it?

358
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:15,386
Yeah. Yeah, I would have
buried it, huh?

359
00:34:15,554 --> 00:34:19,598
- What are you talking about?
- What am I talking about? Come on, bru.

360
00:34:19,766 --> 00:34:21,183
I'm late for work.

361
00:34:21,351 --> 00:34:23,894
Pink, huh? The biggest one
he'd ever seen.

362
00:34:24,062 --> 00:34:26,188
You were in the mining camps,
weren't you, bru?

363
00:34:26,356 --> 00:34:29,859
Why else would that rebel with
the bandaged eye make up such a story?

364
00:34:30,026 --> 00:34:32,278
Go ask him.

365
00:34:46,585 --> 00:34:47,835
Thank you.

366
00:34:57,471 --> 00:35:00,264
Your mothers and fathers,
your brothers and sisters are dead.

367
00:35:00,432 --> 00:35:02,308
- You are dead! You have been reborn.
- No!

368
00:35:02,476 --> 00:35:05,686
- We are your family now.
- No! No!

369
00:35:13,570 --> 00:35:15,905
Your parents are weak.

370
00:35:16,490 --> 00:35:20,910
They're the farmers.
They're the fishermen.

371
00:35:21,411 --> 00:35:24,997
They've done nothing
but suck the blood from this country.

372
00:35:26,374 --> 00:35:30,836
But you are the heroes
who will save this nation.

373
00:35:31,087 --> 00:35:33,047
You are not children anymore.

374
00:35:34,049 --> 00:35:36,008
You're men.

375
00:35:38,220 --> 00:35:41,388
No one has ever given you respect...

376
00:35:41,556 --> 00:35:44,642
...but with this in your hand,
they go fear you.

377
00:35:44,810 --> 00:35:47,311
If you do not get
the respect you deserve...

378
00:35:47,479 --> 00:35:49,772
...you will take it
by shedding their blood.

379
00:35:49,940 --> 00:35:53,901
- Repeat after me, shed their blood.
- Shed their blood.

380
00:35:54,069 --> 00:35:57,154
- Louder! Shed their blood! Shed their blood!
- Shed their blood!

381
00:35:57,322 --> 00:36:00,449
Make them hear you in Freetown.
Shed their blood! Shed their blood!

382
00:36:00,617 --> 00:36:03,202
Shed their blood! Shed their blood!
Shed their blood!

383
00:36:03,370 --> 00:36:06,247
- Dia Vandy, stand up.
- Shed their blood! Shed their blood!

384
00:36:06,414 --> 00:36:09,333
- Shed their blood! Shed their blood!
- Put your hand on the gun.

385
00:36:09,501 --> 00:36:12,878
Shed their blood!
Shed their blood!

386
00:36:13,046 --> 00:36:16,090
- Shed their blood! Shed their blood!
- Now squeeze the trigger.

387
00:36:16,591 --> 00:36:21,011
Come on, Dia. Pull the trigger.
Pull the trigger!

388
00:36:55,130 --> 00:36:59,717
I know, I know.
It's hard to be a man.

389
00:37:00,468 --> 00:37:02,970
Sit up. Come.

390
00:37:03,138 --> 00:37:07,474
But you are a soldier
of the revolution now.

391
00:37:07,642 --> 00:37:10,519
And I am your commander.

392
00:37:11,021 --> 00:37:12,897
Whatever you need...

393
00:37:13,064 --> 00:37:16,317
...guns, CDs, food...

394
00:37:16,484 --> 00:37:20,154
...come to me.
I will take care of you.

395
00:37:23,450 --> 00:37:29,830
Today, you are promoted
to the rank of captain.

396
00:37:34,461 --> 00:37:36,462
Dia Vandy...

397
00:37:38,048 --> 00:37:39,882
...boss man.

398
00:37:57,651 --> 00:37:59,276
How's it, bru?

399
00:37:59,819 --> 00:38:02,988
- You got something for me, huh?
- Yeah.

400
00:38:03,740 --> 00:38:07,159
- So, what's new, M'Ed?
- Fucking RUF.

401
00:38:07,327 --> 00:38:09,870
Tried to hit the government building
across the street.

402
00:38:10,038 --> 00:38:14,708
Shit, man, half the people
be soldiers today, RUF tomorrow.

403
00:38:14,876 --> 00:38:18,253
- Might be time to get your family out, huh?
- And go where?

404
00:38:18,421 --> 00:38:22,174
Just fire up the chopper
and fly away like you people?

405
00:38:22,550 --> 00:38:24,385
This my country, man.

406
00:38:24,552 --> 00:38:28,013
We here long before you came,
long after you gone.

407
00:38:37,023 --> 00:38:40,192
- Hi. I'm Maddy Bowen.
- How about you dance with me?

408
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:43,737
- No, I don't dance.
- Neither do I. Come on.

409
00:38:48,910 --> 00:38:51,328
- So, Danny...
- Archer.

410
00:38:51,621 --> 00:38:52,705
Archer.

411
00:38:53,707 --> 00:38:57,251
When did you first start
moving stones? Was it Angola?

412
00:38:59,045 --> 00:39:03,632
Then you did the whole
mercenary thing. Was that fun?

413
00:39:05,176 --> 00:39:08,846
So, what are you?
Nihilist? Opportunist?

414
00:39:09,055 --> 00:39:11,181
Maybe I wasn't breast-fed
as a child, huh?

415
00:39:13,309 --> 00:39:15,769
You think I haven't met
people like you before?

416
00:39:15,937 --> 00:39:19,273
- I think you get off on people like me.
- You think?

417
00:39:22,027 --> 00:39:24,570
When did you first start
working for Van De Kaap?

418
00:39:25,113 --> 00:39:26,780
Christ, you never stop, do you?

419
00:39:28,033 --> 00:39:31,410
No, I never stop.

420
00:39:32,120 --> 00:39:33,704
Do you want me to stop?

421
00:39:35,081 --> 00:39:38,959
Why don't we go back to your place,
see what's in the minibar, huh?

422
00:39:39,127 --> 00:39:41,253
I'm a print journalist. I drank it.

423
00:39:42,505 --> 00:39:45,257
Is it possible that you don't care
how many people die...

424
00:39:45,425 --> 00:39:47,301
...because of the deals you do?

425
00:39:47,469 --> 00:39:50,721
People here kill each other as a way of life.
Always been like that.

426
00:39:50,972 --> 00:39:53,807
So you can just watch it
and go about your day?

427
00:39:55,143 --> 00:39:57,227
Maybe we should all just
write about it, then.

428
00:39:57,395 --> 00:39:59,730
Look, thanks for the dance, huh?

429
00:40:01,941 --> 00:40:05,319
- And a shot too, huh, M'Ed?
- Sure.

430
00:40:09,157 --> 00:40:10,449
You're a hard case, huh?

431
00:40:10,617 --> 00:40:13,619
Tell me something,
how long you been here in Africa, huh?

432
00:40:13,828 --> 00:40:17,122
Three months. And before that,
Afghanistan and Bosnia.

433
00:40:17,415 --> 00:40:19,500
You come here
with your laptop computer...

434
00:40:19,667 --> 00:40:23,629
...and your malaria medicine
and your little bottles of hand sanitizer.

435
00:40:24,380 --> 00:40:27,424
Think you're gonna change
the outcome, huh?

436
00:40:27,592 --> 00:40:30,177
Let me tell you something.
You sell blood diamonds too.

437
00:40:30,345 --> 00:40:31,845
- Really?
- Yeah.

438
00:40:32,013 --> 00:40:33,013
Tell me, how is that?

439
00:40:33,181 --> 00:40:35,474
Who do you think buys
the stones that I bring out?

440
00:40:35,642 --> 00:40:39,269
Dreamy American girls who all want
a storybook wedding and a big, shiny rock...

441
00:40:39,437 --> 00:40:43,023
...like the ones in the advertisements
of your politically-correct magazines.

442
00:40:43,191 --> 00:40:46,193
So, please, don't come here
and make judgments on me, all right?

443
00:40:47,570 --> 00:40:51,865
I provide a service. The world wants what
we have, and they want it cheap.

444
00:40:52,033 --> 00:40:55,285
We're in business together.
Get over yourself, darling.

445
00:40:55,745 --> 00:40:59,873
Okay, just to clarify, not all American girls
want a storybook wedding...

446
00:41:00,041 --> 00:41:02,918
...just like not all Africans kill each other
as a way of life.

447
00:41:03,086 --> 00:41:05,504
And yeah, it's a shit, shit world,
but you know what?

448
00:41:05,672 --> 00:41:09,550
Good things are done every day,
just, apparently, not by you.

449
00:41:11,136 --> 00:41:14,179
This place is about to explode.

450
00:41:14,430 --> 00:41:16,473
I wanna spend my time
with someone else.

451
00:41:27,569 --> 00:41:30,571
You are listening to BBC World Service.

452
00:41:30,738 --> 00:41:34,491
In Sierra Leone, Revolutionary United Front
forces have been sighted...

453
00:41:34,659 --> 00:41:37,411
...within 10 kilometers
of the capital city of Freetown.

454
00:41:37,579 --> 00:41:40,247
The minister of the interior
has expressed confidence...

455
00:41:40,415 --> 00:41:42,749
...that the government troops
can repel the attack.

456
00:41:42,917 --> 00:41:46,211
All foreign nationals are being advised
to leave the country.

457
00:41:46,379 --> 00:41:48,547
There are also unconfirmed reports...

458
00:41:48,715 --> 00:41:52,759
...that atrocities are being committed by
both sides in the rapidly worsening situation.

459
00:41:52,927 --> 00:41:56,889
The United Nations has described
the refugee situation as critical.

460
00:42:08,443 --> 00:42:10,861
Don't tell me you're gonna try
and sell it yourself.

461
00:42:11,029 --> 00:42:13,572
To who?
And for what price, my friend?

462
00:42:13,740 --> 00:42:15,782
You need my help,
whether you like it or not.

463
00:42:15,950 --> 00:42:18,994
- What are you talking about?
- Here, let me help you with that.

464
00:42:19,162 --> 00:42:23,040
You hear that? You hear that?
They came into the city overnight.

465
00:42:23,208 --> 00:42:25,500
It's started.
What are you gonna do now, huh?

466
00:42:25,668 --> 00:42:29,963
Listen, the right stone can buy anything.
Information, safety, even freedom.

467
00:42:30,131 --> 00:42:32,591
But a big stone does not stay secret
for very long.

468
00:42:32,759 --> 00:42:36,011
The moment you tell anyone about it,
your life is absolutely worthless.

469
00:42:36,179 --> 00:42:39,306
The only reason you're alive is
you haven't told anyone where it is.

470
00:42:39,474 --> 00:42:40,766
Am I right? Am I?

471
00:42:41,142 --> 00:42:43,185
Who do you think got you
out of jail, huh?

472
00:42:43,353 --> 00:42:46,438
- That makes us partners.
- I am not your partner!

473
00:42:46,606 --> 00:42:49,107
What if I helped you find your family?

474
00:42:49,275 --> 00:42:50,817
What do you know of my family?

475
00:42:50,985 --> 00:42:53,987
The relief agencies are useless,
the hospitals are overwhelmed.

476
00:42:54,155 --> 00:42:56,782
- There are other ways, bru.
- Liar.

477
00:42:56,950 --> 00:43:00,160
Look at me. I know people, huh?
White people.

478
00:43:00,328 --> 00:43:03,497
Without me, you're just another
black man in Africa, all right?

479
00:43:06,834 --> 00:43:08,585
