in a constant state of crisis.

830
01:14:52,488 --> 01:14:54,739
Maybe I just give a shit.

831
01:14:58,411 --> 01:14:59,411
You were good today.

832
01:15:01,873 --> 01:15:03,206
You know that?

833
01:15:04,333 --> 01:15:05,834
You too.

834
01:15:08,754 --> 01:15:11,715
"- that sometimes they forgot
to close the door.

835
01:15:11,883 --> 01:15:14,926
She also wrote
about her sister Josie...

836
01:15:15,553 --> 01:15:20,557
...who was very ill
and who had to be taken to hospital. "

837
01:15:22,602 --> 01:15:23,768
Cheers.

838
01:15:26,606 --> 01:15:29,191
So how many attacks
have there been in the area?

839
01:15:29,358 --> 01:15:32,277
I have known most of the rebels
since they were children.

840
01:15:32,445 --> 01:15:36,948
The local commander is still afraid
I will come after him with my ruler.

841
01:15:38,409 --> 01:15:41,870
So you think because your intentions
are good, they'll spare you, huh?

842
01:15:42,038 --> 01:15:44,873
My heart always told me
that people are inherently good.

843
01:15:45,041 --> 01:15:47,250
My experience suggests otherwise.

844
01:15:47,418 --> 01:15:49,211
But what about you, Mr. Archer?

845
01:15:49,629 --> 01:15:52,088
In your long career as a journalist...

846
01:15:52,256 --> 01:15:55,091
...would you say that people
are mostly good?

847
01:15:57,136 --> 01:15:58,595
No.

848
01:15:58,846 --> 01:16:00,388
I'd say they're just people.

849
01:16:00,556 --> 01:16:04,476
Exactly. It is what they do
that makes them good or bad.

850
01:16:04,644 --> 01:16:07,896
A moment of love,
even in a bad man...

851
01:16:08,147 --> 01:16:10,649
...can give meaning to a life.

852
01:16:10,816 --> 01:16:14,444
None of us knows which path
