864
01:17:49,415 --> 01:17:50,874
Then you joined the army?

865
01:17:53,753 --> 01:17:55,920
Yeah. Yeah, I did my time in Angola.

866
01:17:56,088 --> 01:17:58,757
- The 32 Battalion.
- That's right.

867
01:18:01,135 --> 01:18:04,429
You know, contrary to what
you might think about us...

868
01:18:04,597 --> 01:18:08,099
...we fought with the blacks, huh?
Yeah. Side by side.

869
01:18:08,267 --> 01:18:11,978
There was no apartheid in a foxhole.
The colonel always used to tell us that.

870
01:18:12,146 --> 01:18:15,565
- This is Colonel Coetzee?
- Yeah.

871
01:18:17,777 --> 01:18:21,196
Then, of course, it's 1994.
No more army.

872
01:18:21,364 --> 01:18:23,198
No more apartheid.

873
01:18:23,366 --> 01:18:26,743
Truth and reconciliation
and all of that rubbish, you know.

874
01:18:26,911 --> 01:18:28,411
Kumbaya.

