01:25:07,019 --> 01:25:09,687
...on the cover of Soldier of Fortune
magazine for me.

966
01:25:15,694 --> 01:25:16,944
You're going in.

967
01:25:21,366 --> 01:25:23,618
You and Solomon.

968
01:25:25,788 --> 01:25:26,788
You're going in now.

969
01:25:27,623 --> 01:25:29,832
Your plane leaves
in a few minutes, huh?

970
01:25:32,419 --> 01:25:34,378
You're an idiot.

971
01:25:38,717 --> 01:25:41,552
- What if I wanted to go in with you?
- I'd say no.

972
01:25:41,720 --> 01:25:43,721
- What if I insist?
- I'd insist back.

973
01:25:49,853 --> 01:25:51,062
It's my story.

974
01:25:51,230 --> 01:25:54,607
Your story is Van De Kaap, all right?
That stone is mine.

975
01:25:54,775 --> 01:25:58,236
I'm not leaving here without it,
you understand?

976
01:25:59,696 --> 01:26:02,573
Please, just give me two minutes.

977
01:26:19,299 --> 01:26:20,716
Yeah.

978
01:26:32,020 --> 01:26:33,729
- Hello.
- Hi.

979
01:26:33,897 --> 01:26:37,108
My name is Maddy Bowen.
I'm with Vital Affairs magazine.

980
01:26:37,276 --> 01:26:39,777
I was wondering
if I could ask you a few questions.

981
01:26:39,945 --> 01:26:41,445
Well, that depends what they are.

982
01:26:41,613 --> 01:26:45,616
Oh, I see you're familiar
with our devious ways, aren't you?

983
01:26:46,326 --> 01:26:48,244
Okay, so I'll start
with something simple.

984
01:27:00,841 --> 01:27:03,509
And before that you were with
the South African Defense-?

985
01:27:03,677 --> 01:27:05,344
- Defense Force, correct.
- Of course.

986
01:27:05,512 --> 01:27:08,973
And was that with Colonel Coetzee?
Were you in Angola?

987
01:27:09,141 --> 01:27:10,641
Angola, yeah.

988
01:27:12,269 --> 01:27:15,229
That is all I really need to know.
Thank you so much.

989
01:27:15,439 --> 01:27:16,898
- Thank you.
- Okay.

990
01:27:26,909 --> 01:27:28,326
Thank you, huh?

991
01:27:28,493 --> 01:27:30,912
Just keeping my end of the deal.

992
01:27:31,496 --> 01:27:32,830
Good luck to you, Solomon.

993
01:27:33,123 --> 01:27:34,624
Okay.

994
01:27:35,792 --> 01:27:39,629
- I hope you find what you're looking for.
- Thank you for all you have done.

995
01:27:47,054 --> 01:27:49,680
- Listen, I-
- No, you listen.

996
01:27:54,269 --> 01:27:56,187
In another life maybe, all right?

997
01:27:57,606 --> 01:27:59,440
Yeah. Sure.

998
01:27:59,608 --> 01:28:00,983
Yeah.

999
01:28:05,322 --> 01:28:07,448
You find yourself a good man,
all right, Maddy?

1000
01:28:13,372 --> 01:28:16,415
You know, I've got three sisters.

1001
01:28:16,583 --> 01:28:19,210
They're all married to good men.

1002
01:28:21,088 --> 01:28:22,171
I prefer my life.

1003
01:28:24,800 --> 01:28:29,261
Here is my office phone...

1004
01:28:29,429 --> 01:28:31,806
...home phone, cell phone.

1005
01:28:33,892 --> 01:28:37,061
I'm used to being pursued,
but what the heck.

1006
01:28:48,240 --> 01:28:50,408
You better get on that plane, huh?

1007
01:28:52,119 --> 01:28:54,036
You should get on that plane.

1008
01:29:02,212 --> 01:29:04,005
So should you.

1009
01:29:10,470 --> 01:29:11,595
You gonna call me?

1010
01:29:15,434 --> 01:29:16,934
Soon as I'm near a phone, yeah.

1011
01:29:17,853 --> 01:29:20,229
Yeah, right.

1012
01:29:42,044 --> 01:29:45,296
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

1013
01:29:49,885 --> 01:29:51,469
Oh, shit.

1014
01:29:51,762 --> 01:29:54,472
Nabil? Yeah, I'll call you
when we get closer, all right?

1015
01:29:54,639 --> 01:29:57,266
You keep me posted. Right.

1016
01:29:57,434 --> 01:30:01,228
All right. I set the pace, huh?
Two-hour marches, five-minute breaks.

1017
01:30:01,396 --> 01:30:05,232
If I hold my hand up like this, you stop.
If I point to the dirt, you lie flat.

1018
01:30:05,400 --> 01:30:08,986
If I say go, you move like your life
depended on it. Understood?

1019
01:30:09,154 --> 01:30:11,822
- Yes, boss.
- Come on.

1020
01:30:22,084 --> 01:30:23,751
Tell me about the stone.

1021
01:30:23,919 --> 01:30:26,545
Is it clear or is it milky?

1022
01:30:26,713 --> 01:30:28,255
Clear.

1023
01:30:28,423 --> 01:30:30,841
And the color, is it strong?

1024
01:30:31,009 --> 01:30:32,218
Does it hold the light?

1025
01:30:32,385 --> 01:30:34,470
It is as you say.

1026
01:30:34,888 --> 01:30:38,057
- About the size of a bird's egg?
- Yes.

1027
01:30:38,225 --> 01:30:42,394
One hundred carats.
Come on, let's pick up the pace.

1028
01:31:23,979 --> 01:31:25,354
Dia!

1029
01:31:27,232 --> 01:31:29,233
Stop the truck!

1030
01:31:29,985 --> 01:31:31,694
I thought it was Dia.

1031
01:32:25,624 --> 01:32:27,166
Wake up.

1032
01:32:29,002 --> 01:32:32,129
Don't worry, they're gone, huh?

1033
01:32:33,465 --> 01:32:36,592
You know, I once had this buddy...

1034
01:32:36,760 --> 01:32:38,636
...named Mabhoko.

1035
01:32:39,387 --> 01:32:42,640
We used to hunt bush meat
together as kids, huh?

1036
01:32:43,433 --> 01:32:44,808
Baboons.

1037
01:32:44,976 --> 01:32:47,811
Baboons, they were
the hardest to catch. They're...

1038
01:32:48,939 --> 01:32:50,272
They're cunning.

1039
01:32:50,440 --> 01:32:52,524
Cunning creatures.

1040
01:32:52,817 --> 01:32:55,444
Fast, strong.

1041
01:32:55,612 --> 01:32:57,821
Got good eyesight.

1042
01:32:58,323 --> 01:33:02,368
We would always find them
by the smell of their shit.

1043
01:33:02,535 --> 01:33:07,665
And that's how we learned to track
your black terrorists in Angola, huh?

1044
01:33:11,753 --> 01:33:13,170
By the smell of your shit.

1045
01:33:14,214 --> 01:33:15,673
It's not...

1046
01:33:15,840 --> 01:33:18,592
It's not the same as a baboon's.

1047
01:33:20,845 --> 01:33:24,390
But, you know, after you skin it...

1048
01:33:25,684 --> 01:33:27,935
...the flesh of a baboon...

1049
01:33:28,186 --> 01:33:30,604
...isn't that much different
than a man's, you know.

1050
01:33:34,025 --> 01:33:37,945
I'll tell you, I can track anything.

1051
01:33:50,208 --> 01:33:52,376
You risk my life like that again...

1052
01:33:57,716 --> 01:33:59,883
...and I'll peel your face
back off your head.

1053
01:34:02,387 --> 01:34:04,638
Do you understand?

1054
01:34:12,897 --> 01:34:14,940
Make us a fire.

1055
01:34:48,600 --> 01:34:52,102
Hello my brother. Are you lost?

1056
01:34:52,979 --> 01:34:54,813
We are headed for the mines in Kono.

1057
01:34:56,441 --> 01:35:00,527
You don't want to go that way. The
R.U.F. is in the next village.

1058
01:35:02,030 --> 01:35:03,489
Thank you, my brother.

1059
01:35:04,657 --> 01:35:07,451
And tell the poomui not to shoot me.

1060
01:35:09,704 --> 01:35:12,998
He is crazy for diamonds like everybody else.

1061
01:35:13,500 --> 01:35:15,376
Let's hope they don't discover oil here.

1062
01:35:17,712 --> 01:35:20,798
Then we'd have real problems.

1063
01:35:21,758 --> 01:35:22,800
Thank you, my brother.

1064
01:35:25,220 --> 01:35:26,804
What'd he say?

1065
01:35:26,971 --> 01:35:29,139
We are going the right way.

1066
01:35:36,272 --> 01:35:38,982
Hold up there, my man.
It's this way, huh?

1067
01:35:40,485 --> 01:35:42,653
Where do you think you are going?

1068
01:35:44,322 --> 01:35:45,989
Stop!

1069
01:35:46,282 --> 01:35:47,991
I said, stop!

1070
01:35:48,410 --> 01:35:49,993
He is not down there, all right?

1071
01:35:51,996 --> 01:35:55,666
All right. You're gonna need
some of that old discipline, huh?

1072
01:35:55,834 --> 01:35:58,127
Now you listen here, my boy,
and you listen well.

1073
01:35:58,294 --> 01:36:00,254
You are not going down there.
Are we clear?

1074
01:36:00,422 --> 01:36:02,047
You are not the master.

1075
01:36:02,215 --> 01:36:05,843
Right now, that is exactly what I am,
and you'd better remember it, Kaffir!

1076
01:36:21,025 --> 01:36:22,359
Don't you fucking move, huh?

1077
01:36:22,527 --> 01:36:24,486
Don't you move. Don't you move, huh?

1078
01:36:24,654 --> 01:36:26,989
- My son is there!
- Your son is gone!

1079
01:36:27,157 --> 01:36:28,490
- He is alive!
- He's gone!

1080
01:36:28,658 --> 01:36:31,201
He's alive! He's there
with those crazy people!

1081
01:36:32,412 --> 01:36:35,873
I am his father! His father!
I should have protected him!

1082
01:36:36,332 --> 01:36:40,210
I must go find him.
I cannot live without knowing!

1083
01:36:40,378 --> 01:36:42,629
Shoot me if you want, but I'm going.

1084
01:36:44,716 --> 01:36:48,218
Why should it matter,
I'm dead already.

1085
01:36:56,060 --> 01:36:58,312
We wait until dark, huh?

1086
01:37:27,467 --> 01:37:28,884
Are you satisfied?

1087
01:37:31,846 --> 01:37:34,389
All right, come on.

1088
01:37:39,103 --> 01:37:41,313
- is fighting for Sierra Leone

1089
01:37:41,481 --> 01:37:44,566
RUF is fighting for Sierra Leone

1090
01:37:44,734 --> 01:37:47,653
Go tell my parents
They may see me no more

1091
01:37:47,820 --> 01:37:50,906
In the battlefield
We're fighting forever

1092
01:37:51,074 --> 01:37:53,951
Go tell my parents
They may see me no more

1093
01:37:54,118 --> 01:37:55,619
In the battlefield...

1094
01:37:58,164 --> 01:38:00,123
You are how old?

1095
01:38:00,291 --> 01:38:02,084
Me? I'm 31.

1096
01:38:02,252 --> 01:38:04,419
And you have no wife?

1097
01:38:04,879 --> 01:38:07,756
- No.
- No children?

1098
01:38:08,925 --> 01:38:10,217
No.

1099
01:38:10,385 --> 01:38:12,010
And no home?

1100
01:38:12,178 --> 01:38:13,845
No.

1101
01:38:14,556 --> 01:38:16,974
But you have money, yes?

1102
01:38:17,141 --> 01:38:19,393
Yeah, some.

1103
01:38:19,561 --> 01:38:21,562
But not enough?

1104
01:38:24,065 --> 01:38:25,649
No.

1105
01:38:26,359 --> 01:38:30,862
If you get this diamond,
you will have enough money, yes?

1106
01:38:32,991 --> 01:38:34,032
Yes.

1107
01:38:34,200 --> 01:38:36,994
Then you will get
a wife and children?

1108
01:38:37,161 --> 01:38:38,579
Probably not, no.

1109
01:38:40,665 --> 01:38:45,294
What?

1110
01:38:45,670 --> 01:38:47,754
I am confused.

1111
01:38:48,840 --> 01:38:50,299
Yeah?

1112
01:38:50,466 --> 01:38:53,260
That makes two of us, my bru.

1113
01:38:55,763 --> 01:38:59,266
Oh, Christ.
I've gotta quit smoking, huh?

1114
01:38:59,851 --> 01:39:01,852
Why don't you?

1115
01:39:02,103 --> 01:39:04,521
I'll tell you what, Solomon.

1116
01:39:04,772 --> 01:39:09,318
You find me this diamond,
and I'll quit right then and there, huh?

1117
01:39:16,701 --> 01:39:19,703
- You were born in Zimbabwe?
- Oh, yeah.

1118
01:39:19,871 --> 01:39:23,040
- Is it beautiful there?
- Sure you're not a reporter?

1119
01:39:23,458 --> 01:39:26,918
Because you ask a hell of a lot
of questions, my man.

1120
01:39:34,552 --> 01:39:38,263
My grandfather told
many stories of war.

1121
01:39:38,514 --> 01:39:41,350
How the Mende fought the Temne.

1122
01:39:41,517 --> 01:39:45,228
Or how two tribes would fight
when somebody had stolen a woman.

1123
01:39:55,323 --> 01:39:58,700
I understand white people
want our diamonds, yes?

1124
01:40:01,746 --> 01:40:05,457
But how can my own people
do this to each other?

1125
01:40:13,758 --> 01:40:15,801
I know good people...

1126
01:40:15,968 --> 01:40:18,845
...who say there is something
wrong with us...

1127
01:40:19,222 --> 01:40:20,389
...inside our black skin.

1128
01:40:20,556 --> 01:40:23,892
That we were better off
when the white man ruled.

1129
01:40:25,770 --> 01:40:28,605
But my son is good.

1130
01:40:30,149 --> 01:40:32,359
And when he grows up...

1131
01:40:32,527 --> 01:40:33,777
...and peace comes...

1132
01:40:37,782 --> 01:40:40,450
...this place will be a paradise.

1133
01:40:48,292 --> 01:40:50,794
We'll get your son back, huh?

1134
01:41:32,503 --> 01:41:34,838
Where is it exactly?

1135
01:41:36,340 --> 01:41:39,259
Through the camp, by the river.

1136
01:41:43,848 --> 01:41:45,557
Christ.

1137
01:41:46,017 --> 01:41:47,684
Okay.

1138
01:41:48,311 --> 01:41:50,187
I'm gonna make contact
with the colonel.

1139
01:41:50,354 --> 01:41:51,855
He'll send in an air strike.

1140
01:41:52,315 --> 01:41:55,275
- What is that?
- A chopper, huh? An attack helicopter.

1141
01:41:55,443 --> 01:41:57,986
- We use it as a diversion.
- What if my son is there?

1142
01:41:58,154 --> 01:41:59,446
- He isn't.
- How do you know?

1143
01:41:59,614 --> 01:42:03,200
I said we do it my way now, all right?
Don't fuck with me.

1144
01:42:13,127 --> 01:42:15,545
Cordell, it's Danny.

1145
01:42:15,713 --> 01:42:18,048
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Shut up and listen, all right?

1146
01:42:18,216 --> 01:42:21,051
You tell the colonel I've found the stone.

1147
01:42:21,219 --> 01:42:24,221
No, I haven't got it in my hands,
but I'm OP-ing its location.

1148
01:42:24,388 --> 01:42:25,972
It's a major rebel camp, my man.

1149
01:42:26,140 --> 01:42:28,517
You tell him to send in the dakadak.

1150
01:42:29,060 --> 01:42:31,937
Because I stole a GPS, that's how.

1151
01:42:32,104 --> 01:42:34,689
If you shut up and listen,
I could give the coordinates.

1152
01:42:35,107 --> 01:42:38,151
Zero-nine-zero-five-four-two-four, north.

1153
01:42:38,319 --> 01:42:42,906
Three-two-seven-two-nine
three-zero-five-zero, east.

1154
01:42:43,074 --> 01:42:45,325
I'll call back at midnight to confirm.

1155
01:42:48,079 --> 01:42:51,039
You can look all night,
my friend, right?

1156
01:42:51,207 --> 01:42:53,875
I promise you he is not there.

1157
01:42:59,090 --> 01:43:01,299
They're coming in the morning, all right?

1158
01:43:01,467 --> 01:43:03,927
No movement, my friend. You stay still.

1159
01:43:05,847 --> 01:43:08,265
When it gets dark,
then we move in closer.

1160
01:43:30,454 --> 01:43:33,456
Solomon. Shit.

1161
01:43:44,218 --> 01:43:45,635
I can do it.

1162
01:43:45,803 --> 01:43:46,887
- Help me.
- Help him.

1163
01:43:47,054 --> 01:43:49,139
Thank you, Papa.

1164
01:44:31,057 --> 01:44:33,308
Hey, you smell.

1165
01:44:34,518 --> 01:44:35,977
That's fine.

1166
01:44:48,282 --> 01:44:50,241
- Ready? I'm winning.
- Okay, let's go.

1167
01:44:50,409 --> 01:44:52,077
Play, man.

1168
01:44:53,663 --> 01:44:56,539
- Play. Play the card.
- Play.

1169
01:45:23,359 --> 01:45:24,484
Dia.

1170
01:45:27,530 --> 01:45:29,239
Leave me alone.

1171
01:45:30,241 --> 01:45:33,493
- Dia. I'm your papa. Come with me.
- Hey.

1172
01:45:33,661 --> 01:45:35,412
- Dia.
- Get away from me.

1173
01:45:35,579 --> 01:45:37,372
- Dia. Dia!
- I do not know you. Traitor!

1174
01:45:37,748 --> 01:45:40,250
- Enemy! Enemy!
- What the hell are you doing?

1175
01:45:40,418 --> 01:45:41,626
- What are you doing?
- I don't know you!

1176
01:45:41,794 --> 01:45:43,086
- What's wrong?
- I hate you!

1177
01:45:43,254 --> 01:45:45,005
- Dia, come with me!
- I hate you!

1178
01:45:45,172 --> 01:45:46,715
Get away from me!

1179
01:45:49,176 --> 01:45:51,052
- Get him!
- Don't shoot!

1180
01:45:51,554 --> 01:45:53,763
- Don't shoot! Don't-! Don't shoot!
- I hate you!

1181
01:45:53,931 --> 01:45:55,849
- Fisherman! Traitor!
- Don't shoot!

1182
01:45:56,017 --> 01:45:58,268
Get away from me!

1183
01:46:05,359 --> 01:46:07,527
I knew you would come back.

1184
01:46:07,987 --> 01:46:11,489
I have dug and dug and dug,
but I've found nothing.

1185
01:46:11,657 --> 01:46:13,575
Nothing.

1186
01:46:13,826 --> 01:46:15,326
Dig, dig, dig!

1187
01:46:15,494 --> 01:46:17,787
You will find it for me.

1188
01:46:18,789 --> 01:46:21,082
You will dig up
what you have come back for.

1189
01:46:21,250 --> 01:46:22,292
No.

1190
01:46:22,460 --> 01:46:24,878
Why should the diamond
go to the foreign devils?

1191
01:46:25,629 --> 01:46:28,882
We will use it
to make the country strong.

1192
01:46:29,341 --> 01:46:31,968
RUF is fighting for the people!

1193
01:46:34,305 --> 01:46:37,390
RUF is fighting for Sierra Leone!

1194
01:46:40,227 --> 01:46:41,978
Pick it up.

1195
01:46:43,147 --> 01:46:46,149
Why? You are going to kill me anyway.

1196
01:46:46,317 --> 01:46:49,402
I do not need to kill you,
Solomon Vandy.

1197
01:46:52,239 --> 01:46:54,449
If you do not bring me the diamond...

1198
01:46:54,617 --> 01:46:56,826
...I will find the rest of your family.

1199
01:46:56,994 --> 01:46:59,454
Just as I have found your son.

1200
01:47:00,539 --> 01:47:03,917
I will rape your wife
in front of your eyes...

1201
01:47:04,710 --> 01:47:07,003
...slit her throat...

1202
01:47:07,630 --> 01:47:10,006
...and I will keep your daughters
for myself.

1203
01:47:15,387 --> 01:47:17,847
You think I am a devil...

1204
01:47:18,015 --> 01:47:20,350
...but only because I have lived in hell.

1205
01:47:21,977 --> 01:47:24,646
I want to get out.

1206
01:47:25,231 --> 01:47:27,357
You will help me.

1207
01:47:30,194 --> 01:47:31,486
I don't remember.

1208
01:47:31,654 --> 01:47:34,614
Find it or your family will die!

1209
01:47:35,533 --> 01:47:37,408
Now pick it up!

1210
01:47:52,967 --> 01:47:54,384
- Go!
- Bastards!

1211
01:47:54,552 --> 01:47:55,927
Shoot it!

1212
01:48:00,891 --> 01:48:01,891
Dia!

1213
01:48:13,988 --> 01:48:16,197
Come, boy. Come. This way. This way.

1214
01:48:17,074 --> 01:48:18,283
Dia!

1215
01:48:41,182 --> 01:48:42,765
Colonel, we think Archer's there.

1216
01:48:42,933 --> 01:48:45,768
I don't give a damn who's down there.
Kill them all.

1217
01:48:56,113 --> 01:48:57,405
Dia!

1218
01:49:12,129 --> 01:49:13,463
I'm coming!

1219
01:49:16,967 --> 01:49:18,635
- Dia!
- Bastard!

1220
01:49:41,825 --> 01:49:43,159
No!

1221
01:50:03,264 --> 01:50:04,597
Dia!

1222
01:51:10,831 --> 01:51:13,750
- We found his digger, sir.
- Keep him close.

1223
01:51:15,753 --> 01:51:17,920
- Danny boy.
- Colonel.

1224
01:51:18,088 --> 01:51:21,466
- Thanks for calling it in.
- Yeah, yeah. Always happy to help, huh?

1225
01:51:21,633 --> 01:51:24,969
So where is it? The stone?

1226
01:51:25,137 --> 01:51:27,096
We split, huh? Fifty-fifty, all right?

1227
01:51:27,264 --> 01:51:28,890
Look around you, Danny boy.

1228
01:51:29,058 --> 01:51:32,018
You're not in a position
to be dictating terms.

1229
01:51:32,186 --> 01:51:34,270
Then you will never find it, sir.

1230
01:51:34,438 --> 01:51:36,105
That's correct.

1231
01:51:37,775 --> 01:51:40,401
- But he will.
- Come. Up.

1232
01:51:42,029 --> 01:51:44,280
Introduce me to your digger.

1233
01:51:45,824 --> 01:51:47,492
Solomon Vandy.

1234
01:51:47,659 --> 01:51:49,827
This is Colonel Coetzee.
He wants the diamond.

1235
01:51:49,995 --> 01:51:53,039
- No more than you.
- Fuck.

1236
01:51:53,207 --> 01:51:55,208
You gonna show us where it's hidden?

1237
01:51:57,878 --> 01:51:59,587
Does he speak English?

1238
01:51:59,755 --> 01:52:02,799
He will only tell me, sir.
I promise you that.

1239
01:52:03,634 --> 01:52:06,677
- Let me talk to him, huh?
- Go on.

1240
01:52:13,435 --> 01:52:15,812
All right, my friend.

1241
01:52:15,979 --> 01:52:17,897
End of the line here, huh?

1242
01:52:18,065 --> 01:52:21,317
- You just tell him where it is, all right?
- I do not trust him.

1243
01:52:21,485 --> 01:52:24,946
I don't trust him either,
but we haven't got much of a choice here.

1244
01:52:26,657 --> 01:52:29,784
I promise you
he will shoot us both in the head.

1245
01:52:30,202 --> 01:52:32,995
Right, tell him, huh?
Tell him where it is, huh?

1246
01:52:33,163 --> 01:52:35,748
- Go on. Come on.
- I'm not feeling the love, Danny.

1247
01:52:36,959 --> 01:52:39,794
All right.
No more messing about, all right?

1248
01:52:39,962 --> 01:52:42,964
I said tell him where it is!
Tell him where it is! Now!

1249
01:52:43,132 --> 01:52:44,799
Tell him!

1250
01:52:45,968 --> 01:52:47,760
- No.
- Fucking-

1251
01:52:47,928 --> 01:52:50,638
Danny, there are other ways
to do this, okay?

1252
01:52:50,806 --> 01:52:52,432
Yeah, yeah.

1253
01:53:00,607 --> 01:53:03,609
- If he tells us, do we have a deal, sir?
- Seventy-thirty.

1254
01:53:03,777 --> 01:53:06,195
Sixty-forty. I've already lined up a buyer.

1255
01:53:06,363 --> 01:53:08,030
Agreed.

1256
01:53:13,203 --> 01:53:14,745
Come here.

1257
01:53:17,332 --> 01:53:20,751
This is his son. Vandy will do
whatever you want for his sake, all right?

1258
01:53:20,919 --> 01:53:25,715
Danny, you're a pisser, man. Well done.
Boys, we move out.

1259
01:53:28,469 --> 01:53:30,761
What do you say, Mr. Vandy?

1260
01:53:31,221 --> 01:53:34,140
- You ready to take a walk?
- Come on.

1261
01:53:40,397 --> 01:53:42,023
Come on.

1262
01:53:54,953 --> 01:53:58,080
So who's the buyer?
I'm guessing London.

1263
01:53:58,248 --> 01:54:01,542
Well, they no longer accept
conflict diamonds, huh?

1264
01:54:01,710 --> 01:54:04,170
Wouldn't hurt to interest
some other parties.

1265
01:54:04,713 --> 01:54:07,715
- Start a bidding war.
- What, one war's not enough for you, huh?

1266
01:54:08,634 --> 01:54:10,343
I missed you, Danny.

1267
01:54:10,636 --> 01:54:14,805
See? It is here.
He has tried to find it.

1268
01:54:14,973 --> 01:54:17,683
All right, Mr. Vandy.
Time for you to start digging.

1269
01:54:32,741 --> 01:54:34,992
Hey, boet, have you got a smoke?

1270
01:54:35,452 --> 01:54:37,370
Smoking will kill you.

1271
01:54:38,121 --> 01:54:39,622
Sorry.

1272
01:54:42,709 --> 01:54:44,627
It's all right.

1273
01:54:44,795 --> 01:54:46,921
Time I quit smoking anyway,
huh, Solomon?

1274
01:55:01,436 --> 01:55:02,770
- It's gone.
- What?

1275
01:55:02,938 --> 01:55:05,022
Someone has taken it.

1276
01:55:06,149 --> 01:55:09,902
This is where I buried it.
It isn't here.

1277
01:55:10,362 --> 01:55:13,739
Well, then there's no reason
for any of you to stay alive. Is there?

1278
01:55:18,078 --> 01:55:19,745
Wait, wait, wait.

1279
01:55:19,913 --> 01:55:22,164
I know, I know. I know where it is.

1280
01:55:22,624 --> 01:55:24,625
- I know where it is.
- It better be there.

1281
01:55:29,798 --> 01:55:30,798
Yes.

1282
01:55:30,966 --> 01:55:34,343
Oh, here, here.
It is here.

1283
01:55:34,511 --> 01:55:36,178
- Yeah? Yeah, there it is.
- Yes.

1284
01:55:37,347 --> 01:55:38,723
Fuck!

1285
01:55:57,367 --> 01:55:59,327
TIA, huh, Danny?

1286
01:56:00,704 --> 01:56:02,330
TIA.

1287
01:56:09,212 --> 01:56:12,715
Keep digging, huh?
They'll be here any second. Come on.

1288
01:56:14,885 --> 01:56:16,177
Keep digging.

1289
01:56:29,024 --> 01:56:31,734
- It had better be there, huh?
- Yes, yes.

1290
01:56:34,780 --> 01:56:36,405
Have you got it?

1291
01:56:37,824 --> 01:56:41,077
- Have you got it, huh?
- Yes, got it. Oh, yes.

1292
01:56:42,537 --> 01:56:43,788
Oh, yes.

1293
01:56:45,957 --> 01:56:47,583
Solomon.

1294
01:56:54,383 --> 01:56:57,343
Dia, what are you doing?

1295
01:56:57,844 --> 01:56:59,345
Dia.

1296
01:57:00,222 --> 01:57:01,514
Look at me.

1297
01:57:01,682 --> 01:57:03,599
What are you doing?

1298
01:57:06,103 --> 01:57:08,270
You are Dia Vandy.

1299
01:57:08,438 --> 01:57:09,772
Of the proud Mende tribe.

1300
01:57:15,696 --> 01:57:20,574
You are a good boy
who loves soccer and school.

1301
01:57:22,869 --> 01:57:25,996
Your mother loves you so much.

1302
01:57:28,458 --> 01:57:31,252
She waits by the fire making plantains...

1303
01:57:31,420 --> 01:57:34,088
...and red palm oil stew
with your sister N'Yanda...

1304
01:57:36,341 --> 01:57:38,634
...and the new baby.

1305
01:57:47,519 --> 01:57:49,812
The cows wait for you.

1306
01:57:49,980 --> 01:57:55,776
And Babu, the wild dog
who minds no one but you.

1307
01:57:58,321 --> 01:58:01,657
I know they made you do bad things...

1308
01:58:01,825 --> 01:58:04,326
...but you are not a bad boy.

1309
01:58:07,497 --> 01:58:09,915
I am your father...

1310
01:58:11,626 --> 01:58:13,919
...who loves you.

1311
01:58:15,172 --> 01:58:18,966
And you will come home with me
and be my son again.

1312
01:58:44,367 --> 01:58:46,744
Solomon, we've got to move, huh?

1313
01:58:46,912 --> 01:58:48,496
We've got to-

1314
01:58:51,666 --> 01:58:54,376
Go, go! Move!

1315
01:58:57,130 --> 01:58:58,714
Move. Move.

1316
01:58:58,882 --> 01:59:00,174
Move, move, move!

1317
01:59:00,342 --> 01:59:03,385
Move! Move! Move!

1318
01:59:04,971 --> 01:59:06,222
How far?

1319
01:59:06,389 --> 01:59:08,432
There's an airstrip
at the top of that gorge.

1320
01:59:08,600 --> 01:59:10,726
A plane will meet us, huh?

1321
01:59:11,102 --> 01:59:13,479
Hey, stop. Stop.

1322
01:59:15,732 --> 01:59:19,735
Give it to me.
Come on, give it to me, huh?

1323
01:59:27,244 --> 01:59:30,329
Keep moving. They'll be tracking us.

1324
01:59:36,628 --> 01:59:38,712
Nabil, where are you?

1325
01:59:39,756 --> 01:59:42,424
I'm nearly there.
Tell me what's happening.

1326
01:59:42,592 --> 01:59:46,053
We're about 10 K's out, huh?
We've got it, my friend.

1327
01:59:46,221 --> 01:59:48,097
- Who is we?
- The fisherman and his son.

1328
01:59:48,265 --> 01:59:49,890
Lose them.

1329
02:00:04,030 --> 02:00:06,115
It's at the top of that ridge there, huh?

1330
02:00:06,283 --> 02:00:07,616
You must stop and rest.

1331
02:00:07,784 --> 02:00:10,619
What? And give up the damn stone?

1332
02:00:10,787 --> 02:00:12,830
Keep moving. Come on.

1333
02:00:47,490 --> 02:00:49,825
Come. Come, come.

1334
02:01:36,915 --> 02:01:39,208
I can't. Stop.

1335
02:01:39,376 --> 02:01:41,460
- Okay.
- Stop.

1336
02:02:09,906 --> 02:02:11,031
Come on.

1337
02:02:11,616 --> 02:02:14,243
No! God, no. Stop.

1338
02:02:15,328 --> 02:02:18,664
Christ. No more. No more.

1339
02:03:02,625 --> 02:03:04,293
Take it, huh?

1340
02:03:06,713 --> 02:03:09,923
- Mr. Archer-
- Take it, take it.

1341
02:03:16,973 --> 02:03:18,766
I thought you would steal it from me.

1342
02:03:20,602 --> 02:03:24,229
Yeah, yeah, it occurred to me, huh?

1343
02:03:35,158 --> 02:03:36,825
Listen...

1344
02:03:39,788 --> 02:03:42,164
...this is Maddy's card, huh?

1345
02:03:42,332 --> 02:03:44,500
You call her when
you get to Conakry, all right?

1346
02:03:48,755 --> 02:03:50,714
And don't trust that pilot for a second.

1347
02:03:50,882 --> 02:03:53,967
You point this at his head
if he fucks around, all right?

1348
02:03:54,135 --> 02:03:55,594
I can carry you.

1349
02:04:08,525 --> 02:04:09,983
You take your boy home, huh?

1350
02:04:15,156 --> 02:04:17,825
You take him home, huh?

1351
02:04:22,372 --> 02:04:24,123
- Go! Go!
- Go. Come on.

1352
02:04:24,958 --> 02:04:26,041
Go on!

1353
02:04:31,798 --> 02:04:33,674
Come on. Come on.

1354
02:04:40,473 --> 02:04:42,850
Archer, you're a dead man!

1355
02:04:43,017 --> 02:04:44,852
Yeah, yeah.

1356
02:05:15,550 --> 02:05:16,925
Dia.

1357
02:05:38,114 --> 02:05:39,281
Hello. Maddy Bowen.

1358
02:05:39,532 --> 02:05:41,366
Yeah.

1359
02:05:41,701 --> 02:05:43,368
Thought I'd never call, huh?

1360
02:05:44,287 --> 02:05:48,332
And I'm so glad you did.
Excuse me.

1361
02:05:50,293 --> 02:05:51,460
When am I gonna see you?

1362
02:05:52,629 --> 02:05:58,342
Maddy, I want you to do me
one more favor, huh?

1363
02:05:59,052 --> 02:06:03,597
I want you to go meet Solomon
in Conakry.

1364
02:06:03,806 --> 02:06:06,475
In Guinea?
Why do you want me to go to Guinea?

1365
02:06:09,479 --> 02:06:11,563
We found his son...

1366
02:06:12,523 --> 02:06:15,943
...but he's gonna need some help,
you understand?

1367
02:06:16,694 --> 02:06:17,819
Maddy?

1368
02:06:20,615 --> 02:06:22,491
You're hurt.

1369
02:06:23,117 --> 02:06:24,159
Are you hurt?

1370
02:06:24,327 --> 02:06:27,496
Yeah, well, I've got
a little problem here.

1371
02:06:32,085 --> 02:06:35,796
Okay. You-
You tell me where you are.

1372
02:06:39,050 --> 02:06:40,092
Archer?

1373
02:06:52,230 --> 02:06:56,984
I'm looking at an incredible view
right now.

1374
02:06:58,361 --> 02:07:00,028
I wish you were here, Maddy.

1375
02:07:00,196 --> 02:07:03,865
Okay, then I'm coming to be with you.
You just tell me where you are.

1376
02:07:07,036 --> 02:07:08,370
I don't think so.

1377
02:07:08,538 --> 02:07:11,873
Are you still in Kono? Because I can
get someone there to help you.

1378
02:07:12,041 --> 02:07:16,336
Maddy, you find someplace safe
for the boy, all right?

1379
02:07:16,504 --> 02:07:18,880
And keep him out of sight.

1380
02:07:19,507 --> 02:07:22,217
And get Solomon to London.

1381
02:07:25,388 --> 02:07:28,140
He's bringing something with him.

1382
02:07:28,808 --> 02:07:30,726
But he's gonna need your help.

1383
02:07:31,978 --> 02:07:33,812
Why aren't you bringing it yourself?

1384
02:07:35,315 --> 02:07:40,402
I'm saying it's a real story now.

1385
02:07:41,279 --> 02:07:43,030
And you can write the hell out of it.

1386
02:07:50,246 --> 02:07:52,748
I'm really happy I met you.

1387
02:07:54,334 --> 02:07:55,334
You know that?

1388
02:07:58,671 --> 02:08:00,797
Yeah, I'm...

1389
02:08:02,008 --> 02:08:05,093
I'm really happy I met you too.

1390
02:08:05,678 --> 02:08:09,681
And I wish I could be there with you.

1391
02:08:10,558 --> 02:08:12,517
That's all right.

1392
02:08:15,063 --> 02:08:17,439
I'm exactly where I'm supposed to be.

1393
02:09:11,077 --> 02:09:13,412
When we get to the stairs,
you just keep walking...

1394
02:09:13,579 --> 02:09:15,622
...and I'll wait for you here.

1395
02:09:16,165 --> 02:09:17,707
You're not coming.

1396
02:09:17,875 --> 02:09:21,169
I'm not here. Good luck.

1397
02:09:42,817 --> 02:09:45,485
You must understand, Mr. Vandy...

1398
02:09:45,653 --> 02:09:51,700
...that your diamond could have ended up
nowhere else but with us.

1399
02:09:55,037 --> 02:09:57,998
- It is not enough.
- I assure you, 2 million pounds...

1400
02:09:58,166 --> 02:10:02,043
...is more than anyone else will offer you
for that stone under the circumstances.

1401
02:10:02,211 --> 02:10:04,880
I want what was promised to me
by Mr. Archer.

1402
02:10:08,384 --> 02:10:10,886
- What was promised to you?
- My family.

1403
02:10:11,220 --> 02:10:13,221
When they are here,
you will get the stone.

1404
02:10:13,890 --> 02:10:15,557
I will have the money too.

1405
02:10:16,851 --> 02:10:18,393
Well, may I see what I'm buying?

1406
02:10:18,561 --> 02:10:21,313
You will get the stone
once my family is here.

1407
02:10:22,064 --> 02:10:23,899
How do I even know you've got it?

1408
02:12:31,777 --> 02:12:34,529
Can you comment on the diamonds
mined in Sierra Leone?

1409
02:12:34,697 --> 02:12:38,617
I'm not going to comment
on some sensationalist magazine article.

1410
02:12:38,784 --> 02:12:41,369
- What about Liberia?
- No comment. No comment.

1411
02:12:41,537 --> 02:12:43,955
- Mr. Van De Kaap-
- That's all I have to say.

1412
02:12:44,123 --> 02:12:45,540
The natural resources
of a country...

1413
02:12:45,708 --> 02:12:47,375
Kimberley, South Africa
January, 2000

1414
02:12:47,543 --> 02:12:50,503
...are the property of its people.
They are not ours to steal...

1415
02:12:51,839 --> 02:12:57,302
...or exploit in the name of our comfort,
our corporations, or our consumerism.

1416
02:13:07,229 --> 02:13:09,272
They're ready for you, sir.

1417
02:13:10,775 --> 02:13:13,193
The Third World is not a world apart.

1418
02:13:13,361 --> 02:13:18,031
And the witness you will hear today
speaks on its behalf.

1419
02:13:18,199 --> 02:13:22,077
Let us hear the voice of that world.
Let us learn from that voice.

1420
02:13:22,244 --> 02:13:25,747
And let us ignore it no more.

1421
02:13:25,915 --> 02:13:29,250
Ladies and gentlemen,
Mr. Solomon Vandy.



